When composing a document with the Document Composition feature, you may
want to gather statistical information about the parameter values used in
the composite document, or to update databases with the final parameter
values.
This can be achieved by your data collection program (DCP), which is
invoked by the system when document termination processing has been
completed. For example, the document is submitted for deferred printing
and processing continues with another function.
 
The system invokes a DCP if
 
o  The DCP name or transaction code has been defined in the LTD used for
   composition
 
o  At least one parameter defined in one of the selected standard
   paragraphs is marked ("/") as
   "Value is passed to data collection program"
";T

